external_knowledge:
- "Captains of the golden ship" metaphorically refers to the top players;
- "Steering their fortunes with the largest hauls" refers to having the highest total winnings;
- "Across the seas of competition" metaphorically represents the various tournaments.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(tournament_id) AS total_tournaments, tournament_name
FROM tournaments
GROUP BY tournament_name;

SELECT tournament_name 
FROM tournaments 
WHERE prize_pool > (SELECT AVG(prize_pool) FROM tournaments);

external_knowledge:
- Successful players refer to those with the highest total earnings;
- The breakdown of winnings per tournament is calculated by summing up the winnings for each player across all tournaments;
- Top contenders imply the players with the highest ranks, which is limited to the top 5 in this case.

sql:
SELECT hand_id
FROM hand_statistics
WHERE hand_type = 'Best';

SELECT tournament_type, number_of_players, start_time
FROM tournaments
ORDER BY start_time DESC;
